About this item

  • Replacement MAF sensor - Air Flow Sensors (MAFs) measure the amount and characteristics of air entering the engine, providing highly accurate airflow readings to the ECU over a wide range of ambient temperatures, thereby ensuring efficient engine operation. Please clean out the air box and replace the air filter before installing this MAF sensor.
  • Trustworthy Quality - Uses precision elements and high-quality components for enhanced durability and accurate air flow measurements. The MAFs must go through multiple inspections and air flow tests to ensure precise sensor reading and data transmission to the engine system.
  • Ensure fit - Compatible with Infiniti and Nissan Vehicles, 2008-2012 EX35, 2009-2013 FX50, 2003-2008 G35, 2008-2013 G37, 2006-2010 M35, 2014-2019 Q70, 2003-2009 350Z, 2009-2019 370Z, 2003-2014 Altima, 2005-2019 Armada, 2004-2014 Maxima, 2003-2014 Murano, 2012-2019 NV2500/3500, 2004-2015 Pathfinder, 2004-2014 Quest, 2008-2013 Rogue, 2004-2019 Titan, 2007-2019 Versa, 2005-2015 Xterra and more. Please see below vehicle list.
  • Relaces Part # - 22680-7S000, 22680-CA000, 22680-7S00A, 13800-50Z00, AF10141, MAF0031, 245-1117, 917857. The MAF Sensor can easily be located beside the air intake box inside the engine bay.
  • 12-Month Warranty - This mass air flow sensor assembly comes with 12 months warranty, if the sensor ever fails on your car, simply contact us for free replacement or refund. Save time and money off of dealer prices by purchasing this part and taking advantage of our product and services.

Replacement Mass Air Flow Sensor with OE# 22680-7

Replaces Part Numbers:

  • 22680-7S000
  • 22680-CA000
  • 22680-7S00A
  • 13800-50Z00
  • AF10141
  • MAF0031
  • 245-1117
  • 917-857

Features & Benefits:

  • The sensors measure the air mass consumed by the motor as well as the temperature of the air intake
  • Each MAF sensor is double calibrated prior to packaging, assuring the proper output signal during operation
  • All chips are subjected to a high temperature aging test to prevent premature failures
  • Direct fit for a trouble-free replacement

Replacing the MAF sensor can improve fuel efficiency and prevent premature damage to the catalytic converter.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
